Interactive Map of African Capital Cities

This interactive map shows the country boundaries of Africa and marks each capital city using red dots. Hover to see country names or click markers for city info.

# Load Africa boundary data
africa <- rnaturalearth::ne_countries(continent = "Africa", scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf")

# Download global populated places
cities <- rnaturalearth::ne_download(
  scale = "medium",
  type = "populated_places",
  category = "cultural",
  returnclass = "sf"
)
## Reading layer `ne_50m_populated_places' from data source 
##   `C:\Users\HP\AppData\Local\Temp\RtmpqOHacL\ne_50m_populated_places.shp' 
##   using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 1251 features and 137 fields
## Geometry type: POINT
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: -175.2206 ymin: -90 xmax: 179.2166 ymax: 78.22097
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
# Filter only capital cities within African countries
african_capitals <- cities %>%
  filter(ADM0NAME %in% africa$name, FEATURECLA == "Admin-0 capital")

# Create interactive map
leaflet() %>%
  addProviderTiles("CartoDB.Positron") %>%
  addPolygons(
    data = africa,
    fillColor = "lightblue",
    color = "darkblue",
    weight = 1,
    fillOpacity = 0.5,
    label = ~name
  ) %>%
  addCircleMarkers(
    data = african_capitals,
    radius = 5,
    color = "red",
    fillOpacity = 0.8,
    popup = ~paste0("<b>", NAME, "</b><br><i>", ADM0NAME, "</i>")
  )

About

This map was created by Laud Dzandu using R, leaflet, and rnaturalearth. It showcases how spatial data can be turned into intuitive, interactive tools for planning and education.
